''''Cattle station'''' is an [[Australia]]n term for a large farm ([[Station (Australian agriculture)|station]], the equivalent of [[Ranch|ranch]]), usually in the [[outback|outback]], whose main activity is the raising of [[cattle|cattle]].  The owner of a Cattle Station is called a [[Grazier (Australian agriculture)|Grazier]].

Cattle station has a parallel term, [[Sheep station]], for those stations carrying sheep rather than cattle.  In some cases the stations are in a [[rangeland]] context on [[pastoral lease]]s.

The phrase is also in traditional [[Australian English|Australian English]] to denote something large and/or important.


